<subSubSection pageId="17" pageNumber="218" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1436,693,1527]" pageId="17" pageNumber="218">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1355,1380]" pageId="17" pageNumber="218">Remarks.</emphasis>
Specimens from 
<collectingCountry box="[520,602,1355,1380]" name="Bolivia" pageId="17" pageNumber="218">Bolivia</collectingCountry>
slightly differ from Peruvian by their minute (sometimes absent) dorsal forewing white apical ocelli, and a very small dark ocellus in ventral forewing cell M2 (compare 
<figureCitation box="[1228,1295,1391,1416]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="14.[151,250,1869,1891]" captionTargetBox="[228,1320,233,1779]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[189,1364,193,1821]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 5. Adults in dorsal and ventral views. Taxon names appear below each set. Bia rebeli rebeli: a, male, Peru (USNM); b, female, Peru, Huallaga, Tingo Maria (ZSM). Bia rebeli aegina Penz &amp; Simonsen, new ssp.: c, male holotype, Peru, Madre de Dios, Los Amigos Research Center [Puerto Maldonado] (PJD); d, female paratype, same locality (PJD); e, male, Bolivia, Santa Cruz, Buenavista (CMNH); f, female, same locality (CMNH). Intermediate between B. rebeli rebeli and B. rebeli aegina: g, male, Peru, Madre de Dios, Manu, Pakitza (USNM)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/569735/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="218">Figs 5</figureCitation>
e–f with 5c– d). Although examined specimens from 
<collectingCountry box="[639,693,1431,1454]" name="Peru" pageId="17" pageNumber="218">Peru</collectingCountry>
, Manu National Park generally conform to the 
<taxonomicName box="[1281,1436,1430,1454]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Bia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="218" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="rebeli" subSpecies="aegina">
<emphasis box="[1281,1436,1430,1454]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="218">rebeli aegina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
phenotype, one specimen has paler than expected hind wing discal androconial organs (
<figureCitation box="[1159,1228,1466,1491]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="14.[151,250,1869,1891]" captionTargetBox="[228,1320,233,1779]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[189,1364,193,1821]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 5. Adults in dorsal and ventral views. Taxon names appear below each set. Bia rebeli rebeli: a, male, Peru (USNM); b, female, Peru, Huallaga, Tingo Maria (ZSM). Bia rebeli aegina Penz &amp; Simonsen, new ssp.: c, male holotype, Peru, Madre de Dios, Los Amigos Research Center [Puerto Maldonado] (PJD); d, female paratype, same locality (PJD); e, male, Bolivia, Santa Cruz, Buenavista (CMNH); f, female, same locality (CMNH). Intermediate between B. rebeli rebeli and B. rebeli aegina: g, male, Peru, Madre de Dios, Manu, Pakitza (USNM)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/569735/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="218">
Fig. 
<quantity box="[1214,1228,1466,1491]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="kg" metricValue="5.0" pageId="17" pageNumber="218" unit="g" value="5.0">5</quantity>
</figureCitation>
